title: Number of oncology practices in the U.S. by region and size 2013
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
For Country South, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients 75.0 among the 3 groups and in West, 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients 24.0.
There is a gap of 17.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 3-6 physicians in Country West and South.
Averaging all 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians, the Country South is the maximum Number of new patients and Northeast is the minimum Number of new patients.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
Country South had the maximum Number of new patients among all 3 groups, and it was for 7 or more physicians. The minimum Number of new patients was observed in Country West for 1-2 physicians.
For Country West, 3-6 physicians had the maximum Number of new patients and it saw the lowest in Country South out of all 4 Countrys.
Country West and South had the biggest gap of 17.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 3-6 physicians.
Among all 3 groups, 1-2 physicians had the gap of 35.0 between the maximum and minimum Number of new patients observed in Country South and West respectively.

In case of Country South, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients 75.0 among the 3 groups and in West, 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients 24.0. The second highest Number of new patients 59.0 was observed for 7 or more physicians in Country South.
Averaging all 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians, the Country South is the maximum Number of new patients and Northeast is the minimum Number of new patients.
